snippet.description:

INFO:
Kevin de Vries and I have been in touch for years exchanging music and talking about doing a release from him on my labels.
The time has come with this incredible ‚ÄúVertigo‚Äù release.
Needless to say that I‚Äôve been a fan of Kevin‚Äôs sound for years and supporting almost every single release he‚Äôs had.
So I am obviously super happy to finally land his excellent music on NM2.

I feel we‚Äôve put together a release so strong that it sets the bar extremely high for what‚Äôs to come on NM2 in the future.
Kevin‚Äôs flair for making amazing melodies and soundscapes mixed with spot on arrangements and in depth productions is a true pleasure for your ears.
Even when writing these words I slowly drift away and dive into the music with a smile on my face.

To top it all we also got a superb remix from Marco Faraone who has been among my favorite techno producers for years as well and one I have been wanting to release music by for some time. His remix makes ‚Äúvertigo‚Äù a more hard hitting and techno driven
banger.
Cleverly keeping all the melodies intact and wrapped up in heavy beats.

I feel blessed to have both these artists deliver such high quality music for NM2.
This release honestly feels like moving into a new era for the label and excites me so much for the future releases.
-NOIR-

I am really proud to present this first ‚ÄúDEFINED‚Äù series release with productions by former Noir Music artists Olivier Giacomotto, John Monkman, Kiko and Jos & Eli whom all now fits the NM2 imprint and have given me the perfect music to help define the sound of

It is super exciting to move NM2 into a new era of great releases and a more DEFINED sound.
-NOIR-

INFO:
It‚Äôs been a while since I collaborated and produced a song with singer/songwriters. The past 4 years have been very focused on instrumentals. 
But back in 2020, I wrote a track that screamed for vocals. So I reached out to my good friends Hendrik  Burkhard and Anne Kalstrup (RBBTS) and asked them if the instrumental inspired them to write a song on top. Luckily for me, the answer was prompt; YES!
The music was written during the pandemic lockdowns with the intent to express a lot of hope and positivity during the hard times.
Naturally, I asked RBBTS to reflect those feelings with words and harmonies, and the result was even better than I had hoped for.
RBBTS are extremely good at writing beautiful, haunting hooks, and ‚ÄúBefore We Fade‚Äù is a great example of their talent.
 
Today the song resonates with so much more than just isolation.
The idea behind the song is to let the vocals take center stage accompanied by my chords and soundscapes before the tension is 
released in form of hard-hitting beats and an uplifting, constant moving melody. A contrast of the mind is expressed in the music. 

Anne, Hendrik, and I feel we created something special with this song, and we hope it resonates with the listeners and makes them feel the same way.
-NOIR-

snippet.title: NOIR  - The Interview 2015
snippet.description:
Noir Music proudly presents the self-titled studio album from electronic star Noir: one of the mostly hotly anticipated dance music debuts of 2015.

One of the world's most in demand DJs and producers, Noir has been responsible for some of the most poignant ‚Äì as well as explosive ‚Äì moments in clubland‚Äôs recent history. Arguably best known for his huge dancefloor bomb ‚ÄòAround‚Äô, Noir now drops his debut studio album, a project that has been nearly half a decade in the making.
‚ÄòAround‚Äô, a sexy, synthesizer-tinted groove featuring vocalist Hayze dominated dancefloors across the world for close to two years, making Noir a household name across clubland. And it‚Äôs still as popular as ever ‚Äì the Solomon Vox remix of ‚ÄòAround‚Äô has amassed more than 12 million views on YouTube.
As well as ‚ÄòAround‚Äô, Noir includes further club hits ‚ÄòAround feat. Hayze‚Äô, ‚ÄòMy Fault feat. HRRSN‚Äô and current single ‚ÄòBlack feat. Caitlin‚Äô, evidencing Noir‚Äôs desire to work with a variety of vocalists to create something far weightier than simply a collection of club tracks.
Noir is about telling stories, boating 12 completely unique productions that chart the artist‚Äôs evolution over the course of his expansive career.
With many of its cuts moving away from the strict four-to-the-floor parameters of house music production, the horizons of Noir stretch way beyond the dancefloor. Taking cues from a range of artists from Depeche Mode to Kraftwerk, and Massive Attack to Timbaland ‚Äì all of whom have heavily influenced Noir‚Äôs aesthetic ‚Äì Noir is an emotionally charged and utterly engrossing body of work.
Says Noir of working on the album: ‚ÄúThe album has been in the making since I started working on ‚ÄòAround‚Äô back in 2010, so for me it‚Äôs a body of work that spans nearly 5 years, with changes to productions, melodies and moods before I was happy with the final tracks.
‚ÄúWhat you hear on the album is the culmination of all the music and influences I grew up and have lived with over the years: it is absolutely my identity and honestly represents my musical passions. ‚Äú
Unlike many ‚Äòdance‚Äô albums that are little more than a collection of thrown-together club tracks, Noir combines tirelessly creative songwriting with multi-faceted production that reveals fresh delights with every listen: a timeless release from a truly singular artist.

INFO:
It‚Äôs been a while since I collaborated and produced a song with singer/songwriters. The past 4 years have been very focused on instrumentals. 
But back in 2020, I wrote a track that screamed for vocals. So I reached out to my good friends Hendrik  Burkhard and Anne Kalstrup (RBBTS) and asked them if the instrumental inspired them to write a song on top. Luckily for me, the answer was prompt; YES!
The music was written during the pandemic lockdowns with the intent to express a lot of hope and positivity during the hard times.
Naturally, I asked RBBTS to reflect those feelings with words and harmonies, and the result was even better than I had hoped for.
RBBTS are extremely good at writing beautiful, haunting hooks, and ‚ÄúBefore We Fade‚Äù is a great example of their talent.
 
Today the song resonates with so much more than just isolation.
The idea behind the song is to let the vocals take center stage accompanied by my chords and soundscapes before the tension is 
released in form of hard-hitting beats and an uplifting, constant moving melody. A contrast of the mind is expressed in the music. 

Anne, Hendrik, and I feel we created something special with this song, and we hope it resonates with the listeners and makes them feel the same way.
-NOIR-
